args: The time has finally come for the\n313th ＂Most Beautiful Me＂ contest!\nUp first is...me!
And next, we have...me in a mirror!\nBut which is the fairest? Who is\nthe TRUE paragon of beauty?
Hm? It's a draw, you say?\nHa ha! Marvelous!
Man... I dunno how you can do that 313\ntimes an' not get tired of it.
What inspired the change of attire, Zardin?
Ah, but the man before you is not the\nZardin you once knew.
Nay, he is now a beautician!
BEAUtician, my good fellow. 'Tis a most\nelegant profession, tasked with bringing\nout the beauty sealed in every soul.
Naturally I have already ascended to the\nhighest heights of beauty—but with this\nnew charge, I shall climb even higher!
Likewise. You have only explained\nwhat a beautician DOES, and even\nthat was somewhat murky.
How exactly do you think making others\nmore beautiful will elevate yourself?
It's all in the synergy, my dear!

My beauty is already perfection itself.
The question of whether I can grow even
more beautiful enters a hitherto unknown
realm of knowledge.

I ruminated so extensively on how
to transcend my current limits, I
perfected a beautiful contemplative
visage in the process.
And then, I was struck by an epiphany!\nI must make others more comely!
Thus would their beauty amplify my own,\nmaking me more handsome still.
'Tis but a theory, of course, but is that\nnot how all facts are born?
No doubt others have tried and\nfailed spectacularly, but none\nwere as beautiful as I.
So come! Let us ascend together\nto new plains of beauty!
W-wait, where are you taking us?!
Single file, please... Perfect.\nLet us begin!
Uh... What do we do now?
We shall start with the basics.\nHere, rub this gel on your faces.
Massage it in small circles—excellent.\nGently does it.
Oh! It's cold, but also quite refreshing.
All finished? Lovely.\nNow come the exercises!
When I call out an expression,\nyou must produce it as beautifully\nas possible!
That ain't hard, in a situation like this...
Not bad, not bad.\nFinally, give me your portrait face!
This is the expression I made when\nthe portrait artist came to the castle...\nWhat do you think?
YES! Marvelous! Now rotate through all\nthree, one per second, a hundred times!
We are not a comedy troupe!
Hmph. Very well.\nOn to the next activity, so!
More gel for everyone.\nMake sure you rub it in well!
My face feels like someone\nsneezed all over it...
Massage it in deep, and visualize\nyourself beautified!
As it should. Now, repeat the same\nprocess ten thousand times!
Beauty does not come easy. But with\ndiligence and determination, you may\none day shine slightly dimmer than myself.
The steps you just practiced are all\npart of my daily beauty routine.\nSimple, no?
Goodness, such an angry look does\nno favors for your complexion.

My patience is at its end, Zardin.
This routine may work for you,
but it is naught but wasted time
for the rest of us.
Yes, and I have to think using this much\ngel is a waste of money, too.
How's this bringin' out our inner beauty,\nanyhow?
All yer doin' is makin' my face hurt.\nDidja even think this through?
Guys, I think that might've been a\nbit harsh...
I have somehow grown even MORE\nbeautiful in realizing my mistakes!
Yes, I can see the road before me now...
I shall perfect my skills as a beautician,\nand aid all who heed my call!
...Is this guy even safe to have around?
With this outfit and my unmatched resolve,\nI can unlock ANYONE'S true beauty!
I must get to work. Farewell, my students!
Ah, and do remember to wash away\nthe gel when you're finished. Ta ta!
In any case, let's wash this gel off.
I wonder if he really will become\nthe beautician he aspires to be...
